Source: libfreedomevision
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Maintainer: FreeDome Project <freedome@nativemind.dev>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 12), cmake (>= 3.16), pkg-config, libportaudio2, libsndfile1-dev
Standards-Version: 4.5.0
Homepage: https://github.com/freedome/freedomevision

Package: libfreedomevision2
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: FreeDome Vision processing library - runtime
 FreeDome Vision is a quantum-enhanced visual processing library designed 
 for immersive dome projection systems. It provides advanced quantum 
 interference field generation, consciousness hybrid systems, and 
 Lubomir understanding capabilities for professional visual applications.
 .
 This package contains the shared libraries.

Package: libfreedomevision-dev
Architecture: any
Section: libdevel
Depends: libfreedomevision2 (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}, libportaudio2, libsndfile1-dev
Description: FreeDome Vision processing library - development files
 FreeDome Vision is a quantum-enhanced visual processing library designed 
 for immersive dome projection systems. It provides advanced quantum 
 interference field generation, consciousness hybrid systems, and 
 Lubomir understanding capabilities for professional visual applications.
 .
 This package contains the header files and static libraries needed for
 developing applications that use FreeDome Vision.

Package: freedomevision-tools
Architecture: any
Depends: libfreedomevision2 (= ${binary:Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: FreeDome Vision processing tools
 FreeDome Vision is a quantum-enhanced visual processing library designed 
 for immersive dome projection systems.
 .
 This package contains command-line tools and utilities for working with
 FreeDome Vision processing.
